      "IsMRef": true,
      "Title": "Invex.Extensions.Json.JsonExtensions",
      "Summary": "<p sourcefile=\"api/Invex.Extensions.Json.JsonExtensions.yml\" sourcestartlinenumber=\"1\">Extension methods for working with System.Text.Json nodes using a human-readable path notation.</p>\n<p>Path conventions:</p>\n<ul><li>\n            Object properties are separated by a configurable separator, colon by default\n            (e.g., <code>\"user:address:city\"</code>).\n        </li><li>\n            Arrays are addressed with bracketed indices (e.g., <code>\"users:[0]:name\"</code>) in\n            flattened/unflattened keys.\n        </li><li>\n            For in-place replacement via\n            <xref href=\"Invex.Extensions.Json.JsonExtensions.ReplaceValues(System.Text.Json.Nodes.JsonObject%2cSystem.Collections.Generic.Dictionary%7bSystem.String%2cSystem.String%7d%2cSystem.String)\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref>, array steps use\n            bare numeric segments instead (e.g., <code>\"users:0:name\"</code>).\n        </li></ul>\n<p>\n    These helpers are allocation-conscious and designed for clarity when manipulating JSON in config and ETL\n    scenarios.\n</p>\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "ManagedReference",
      "source_relative_path": "api/Invex.Extensions.Json.JsonUtil.yml",
      "output": {
        ".html": {
          "relative_path": "api/Invex.Extensions.Json.JsonUtil.html"
        }
      },
      "version": "",
      "Uid": null,
      "IsMRef": true,
      "Title": "Invex.Extensions.Json.JsonUtil",
      "Summary": "<p sourcefile=\"api/Invex.Extensions.Json.JsonUtil.yml\" sourcestartlinenumber=\"1\">Provides extension members on <xref href=\"System.Text.Json.Nodes.JsonObject\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref> for flattening a hierarchical JSON structure into a\nsingle level and reconstructing (unflattening) it again.</p>\n<p>Path conventions used by this class:</p>\n<ul><li>\n            Object property segments are joined with a configurable separator (default <code>\":\"</code>),\n            e.g., <code>\"user:address:city\"</code>.\n        </li><li>\n            Array elements are addressed with bare zero-based numeric segments, e.g., <code>\"users:0:name\"</code>.\n        </li></ul>\n<p>\n    Note: this differs from <xref href=\"Invex.Extensions.Json.JsonExtensions.Flatten(System.Text.Json.Nodes.JsonNode%2cSystem.String)\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref>, which uses bracketed\n    indices such as <code>\"users:[0]:name\"</code>.\n</p>\n"
    },
